{"Mix the meat, eggs, corn chips, milk, black pepper. Mix well. Then add A-1 Sauce and minced dried onion. Cover and refrigerate at least two hours or overnight.", "In very large saucepan,add olive oil, garlic, chili powder, cumin, green chilies, white onions. Saute until onions are starting to turn brown. Add sugar, tomatoes and olives. Simmer about 15 minutes. Set Aside.", "Form meatballs, about 1 large tblsp. and roll between hands.", "Add flour or cornstarch in pie plate and roll each meat ball. Place on a tray.", 
