{"Pound each steak portion with meat mallet or a plate.", "Note: I use a meat tenderizer utensil with knifes in it.", "Put flour and seasoning in a pie pan, mix.", "Beat eggs with water and pour into another pie pan.", "Dip each piece in beaten eggs, shake the drips back  in the pan.", "Put each pounded piece in seasoned flour, pound in on both sides. Place on a plate.", "Do all pieces once, then if you want to dip a second time, do so. Do not stack the dipped pieces or the coating may come off.", 
