{"{NOTE:", "If you throw in a hunk of salt pork, do not add salt until beans are done and you taste them}.", "Discard any discolored beans.", "In a large bowl, combine the beans with plenty of cold water and soak overnight for 6 to 8 hours.", "Drain the beans.", "In a large pot, combine the beans and enough water to cover them by 1 inch.", "Bring to a boil, lower the heat to simmer, and cook for 45 minutes or until they are just tender {it may take longer if the beans are old or the soaking time was short}.", 
